A woman who has had an unusually deep voice since birth could not cancel her Sky subscription because call centre staff refused to believe she wasn't a man.

Due to abnormally enlarged vocal chords, Norma Clarke, 56, from Eccles, Greater Manchester has spoken like a man for as long as she can remember.

She said: 'When people call the house phone and ask for Mrs Norma Clarke, they don’t believe it’s me.

'I wasn’t able to cancel my Sky package because the person at the other end of the line didn’t believe I was a woman.'

