However, she tries to have a sense of humour about her voice, saying: 'I’m dead outgoing. I like a good chuckle and I like to laugh at myself. Because of that, I’ve been able to overcome all of the stick I get.

'I play jokes on people. I once pretended that I was my friend’s new boyfriend when she was speaking to her brother in Canada on Skype! He completely believed it.'

She is married to medical courier driver, John Clarke, 61, and they have four daughters and six grandchildren. Mrs Clarke says that her voice has never deterred the opposite sex.

She explains: 'I’ve been married twice and I’ve never had any problems with men because of my voice at all. I think they liked that I was a little bit different.'

